olive oil
1 egg
drizzle white wine vinegar
2 Potato
1 Avocado
1 packet Pork Mince
1 packet Fine Breadcrumbs
1 sachet All-American Spice Blend
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
1 packet Garlic Aioli
2 Brioche Hotdog Buns

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut potato into fries, then place on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and toss to coat.
• Spread out evenly, then bake until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, slice avocado in half, scoop out flesh and thinly slice.
• SPICY! This is a mild spice blend, but use less if you’re sensitive to heat! In a medium bowl, combine pork mince, fine breadcrumbs, All-American spice blend, the egg and a pinch of salt.
• Using damp hands, roll heaped spoonfuls of pork mixture into small meatballs (4-5 per person). Transfer to a plate.

• In a large frying pan, heat a generous drizzle of olive oil over
medium-high heat.
• Cook meatballs, turning, until browned and cooked through, 8-10 minutes (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded).
• Meanwhile, combine mixed salad leaves and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil in a second medium bowl. Season.
• While the meatballs are cooking, slice brioche hotdog buns in half lengthways, three quarters of the way through. Bake buns directly on a wire oven rack until heated through, 5-7 minutes.

• Spread garlic aioli on both cut sides of the buns, then fill with pork meatballs, avocado and salad leaves.
• Divide All-American pork meatball subs and fries between plates to serve. Enjoy!